+## Authority Resolution Policy
+
+When a Verilog domain contract rule and a general behavioral rule both apply to the same task,
+they operate at different levels and do not conflict:
+
+- The **Verilog domain contract rules** (System 1) govern RTL-specific precondition gate behavior
+- The **general behavioral rules** (System 2) govern session-level behavioral discipline
+
+Resolution priority:
+1. Defer to Verilog domain contract rule for RTL precondition and completion claim decisions.
+2. Apply the general behavioral rule at the behavioral/output scope level.
+3. If apparent contradiction: Verilog domain contract rule governs RTL output; general rule governs framing.
+
+Explicit conflict not anticipated in v0.1 scope. If observed, escalate per `CMN-001`.
+
